{{Top|ca|leg}}
The '''Galactic Society of Recording Artists''' was a group that managed the collection of royalties due to be paid to its [[Musician/Legends|members]] for the performance of their [[Music/Legends|music]] by other entertainers. [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]], a [[3PO-series protocol droid/Legends|3PO-series]] [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] with access to a myriad of songs for playback in his [[Memory bank/Legends|memory core]], factored in these royalties when determining if he could earn enough money for passage off the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Nim Drovis]] with his [[Counterpart/Legends|counterpart]], an [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]] designated [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]],<ref name="PT">''[[Planet of Twilight]]''</ref> in [[13 ABY/Legends|13 ABY]].<ref name="ERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The Galactic Society of Recording Artists was briefly mentioned in ''[[Planet of Twilight]]'', a [[1997]] novel by [[Barbara Hambly]].<ref name="PT" />

